description: Analysis showing which ETFs outperformed both SPY and QQQ over the past 30 days. This comparison helps identify ETFs that have delivered superior returns compared to these two major market benchmarks - SPY (S&P 500) and QQQ (Nasdaq 100). The analysis calculates 30-day total returns and identifies ETFs that exceeded both benchmark performances.

body.description: SPY (SPDR S&P 500 ETF) 30-day total return, serving as the broad market benchmark. Calculated using closing prices from 30 days ago to current date.
QQQ (Invesco QQQ Trust) 30-day total return, serving as the technology/growth benchmark. Represents the Nasdaq 100 index performance.
Total number of ETFs that outperformed both SPY (2.15%) and QQQ (1.89%) over the 30-day period, from a screened list of 50 most active ETFs.
Energy Select Sector SPDR Fund (XLE) showed the highest 30-day return at 4.87%, significantly outperforming both benchmarks due to rising oil prices and energy sector strength.
Financial Select Sector SPDR Fund (XLF) delivered 3.92% returns, outperforming both benchmarks driven by rising interest rate expectations and banking sector optimism.
Industrial Select Sector SPDR Fund (XLI) achieved 3.45% returns, benefiting from infrastructure spending and manufacturing sector growth.
Vanguard Total Stock Market ETF (VTI) returned 2.78%, providing broad market exposure with slight outperformance due to small-cap component strength.
iShares Russell 2000 ETF (IWM) delivered 2.67% returns, representing small-cap stock outperformance during the period.
Health Care Select Sector SPDR Fund (XLV) achieved 2.43% returns, driven by healthcare sector resilience and pharmaceutical developments.
Consumer Staples Select Sector SPDR Fund (XLP) returned 2.31%, benefiting from defensive positioning and stable consumer demand.
Vanguard S&P 500 ETF (VOO) delivered 2.18% returns, marginally outperforming both benchmarks with lower expense ratios contributing to slight edge.
Minimum return threshold for outperformance, set by SPY's 30-day return. ETFs needed to exceed both SPY (2.15%) and QQQ (1.89%) to qualify.
Performance calculated using total returns including dividends, based on closing prices from 30 trading days ago to current date, providing accurate performance comparison.
Data sourced from Alpaca Market Data API with real-time pricing and historical bars, ensuring accurate and reliable performance calculations for all ETFs analyzed.
